# paint.type AI Manifest (Level 1)

This is the AI manifest for the `docs/` directory (Level 1) of paint.type.

## Purpose

This manifest describes the purpose and structure of the `docs/` directory.

## Authority Split

- **Central protocol authority:** `standards/` repository
- **Local integration authority (this directory):** docs/ specific configurations

## Subdirectories\n\n| Directory | Layer | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `practice/` | 2 | |\n| `standards/` | 2 | |\n| `legal/` | 2 | |\n| `attribution/` | 2 | |\n| `whitepapers/` | 2 | |\n| `theory/` | 2 | |\n| `reports/` | 2 | |\n| `decisions/` | 2 | |\n| `superpowers/` | 2 | |\n| `wikis/` | 2 | |\n| `templates/` | 2 | |\n| `developer/` | 2 | |\n| `architecture/` | 2 | |\n| `governance/` | 2 | |\n| `wiki/` | 2 | |\n\n## Canonical Files\n\n- `STATE-VISUALIZER.adoc` -- AsciiDoc documentation\n- `QUICKSTART.adoc` -- AsciiDoc documentation\n- `RSR_OUTLINE.adoc` -- AsciiDoc documentation\n- `tech-debt-2026-05-26.md` -- Markdown documentation\n\n## Invariants

1. All A2ML state files must live in `.machine_readable/` ONLY, never in the repo root.
2. Each directory at layer 1 must have its own `0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
3. Each directory must have a `README.adoc` describing purpose, contents, and function.
4. SPDX license identifiers must be consistent across all files (AGPL-3.0-or-later).

## Startup Checklist for Agents

1. Read this file (`0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`).
2. Read `README.adoc` for directory overview.
3. For subdirectories, navigate to their respective manifest files.
4. Never edit `.machine_readable/` files directly.
